On Friday, ODM leader Raila Odinga turned 77, and his supporters have taken it upon themselves to organise various celebrations across the country. Notably, his main State House rival, Deputy President William Ruto has not been left behind in celebrating the man regarded as the father of democracy in Kenya. Through his official Twitter account, Ruto sent his birthday message to the former Prime Minister, saying that he be blessed with many more years. Elected leaders from across the political divides have also celebrated Raila in their own ways with a majority sharing the messages on social media. Here are some of their wishes; Edited by D Tarus